ceph (0.67.2-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=low

  * New upstream release.
  * Update debian/copyright .
  * Sync with Ubuntu.

  [ James Page <james.page@ubuntu.com> ]
  * debian/control,rules,libcephfs-{java,jni}: Enable Java CephFS library,
      add new BD's on javahelper and default-jdk, add dbg package.
  * debian/control: Add new BD on libboost-thread-dev for RADOS Gateway
      keystone integration.
  * debian/{control,obsync.install}: Drop obsync package inline with
      upstream.
  * debian/librbd-dev.install: Pickup new features.h file.
  * Remove manual calls to ldconfig (LP: #1017978):
    - debian/lib{rados2|rbd1|cephfs1}.post*: Dropped - all these do is call
      ldconfig which will automatically be done. 
    - debian/rules: Let dh_makeshlibs do its magic with postinst/postrm
      scripts but ensure that the .so's in ceph package are excluded.
  * debian/patches/pthread-linking.patch: Fix indirect pthread linking problem
    for librados-config.
  * d/tests/*: Added autopkgtests for librbd, librados, python-ceph
    and the ceph CLI.

  [ Bastian Blank ]
  * Use debhelper 9.
  * Use dh-autoreconf.
  * Install files from source tree if possible.
  * Run test-suite:
    - Build-depend on python-virtualenv.
    - Ask virtualenv to never download anything.
  * Fix clean target.
  * Properly mark library modules:
    - Don't longer exclude them from stripping.

 -- Laszlo Boszormenyi (GCS) <gcs@debian.org>  Sun, 08 Sep 2013 10:10:42 +0200

ceph (0.48-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream release, the first with long-term support.
  * As gceph dropped by upstream, remove it from packaging.
  * Build with hardening enabled and build-conflict with libcryptopp not to
    mix up with libnss.
  * Use symbol versioning (closes: #679686).
  * Update debian/watch to GitHub tags.

